**Univariate Normal distribution:**

\[
X \sim \mathcal{N}(\mu, \sigma^2)
\]

mean: \( \mu \)  
variance: \( \sigma^2 \)

\[
p(x | \mu, \sigma^2) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi\sigma^2}} \exp\left( - \frac{(x - \mu)^2}{2\sigma^2} \right)
\]
